Anthony Gordon missed a chance to equalize two minutes after the goal
Harry Kane missed a golden chance in the 28th minute

Kolbeinn Finnsson attempted an audacious volley from the edge of the box
Pre-Game Insights: England were booed off by some of their own fans
Iceland did not qualify for the Euros and were beaten by Ukraine in their playoff final in March
Post-Match Reflections: England captain Harry Kane missed a golden chance in the 28th minute
England looked flat in their final game before the Euros in Germany
Centre-back John Stones appeared to roll his ankle and was replaced at half-time
Manager Gareth Southgate played down the severity of John Stones' injury
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match took place at Wembley Stadium
